$interpreted: Jahan: Heh, this forsaken place. Desolate, as it always was.
Dylan: Sir Augustinus?
Jahan: Don't be shy. Sione told me everything.
Jahan: Either kowtow or lick the soles of my boots. Live or die, make your choice~
Dylan: Sione, what's this all about?
Sione: Colonel. The case has been solved. Cecil's coin sack was afforded by Jahan.
Dylan: As I suspected, Truth is stranger than fiction. Why does it match with the kidnappers' coin sack....
Jahan: Coin-Coin sack? What are you yammering about? Weren't you supposed to offer me your most humble apology, and beg for my forgiveness?
Jahan: B-B-Boring!! I'm leaving!
Dylan: I don't think so! Not until you come clean!
Cecil: Sir Augustinus!
Jahan: Vincent, HELP ME!
Cecil: Sunshine Infantry has turned its back upon our nation. You asked for this! Everybody, CHARGE!
Sione: SPEAK! The princess' kidnappers...did you give them the coin sacks they carried?
Jahan: Damn, damned woman, get your filthy hands off of me! I have the right to remain silent!
Dylan: How about, if I was the one interrogating...?
Jahan: Eh? Now hold it...AH HELP ME!
Dylan: Let me get this straight. You made these coin sacks, down to each stitch?
Dylan: No wonder. Every seamster and seamstress across the land wouldn't admit to this crappy handiwork...
Jahan: Yes...anyone who completes a request of mine, will receive both payment and my unique coin sack.
Dylan: Who instructed you to kidnap the princess?
Jahan: It was His M-M-Majesty, King Theodore...I had no choice but to comply...
Sione: Theodore!? Colonel, what the hell are we supposed to do?
Dylan: We have our witness, but getting him to testify openly against Theodore...
Sunshine Solider: Colonel! Colonel Levon!
Sunshine Solider: Terrible news, our allies have reported that the castle...the castle has begun to fly!
Sione: WHAT?!
